#Laser range data generated by :

# Generate robot motion and laser angles
player ../player_worlds/simple.cfg &

# capture data to laser_pose_all.bin laser_ranges_all.bin scan_angles_all.bin
../../bin/captureplayerdata

# Above capture causes all reflectance values to be false. to fix this we
# regenerate simulated ranges and reflectance with following script
../../bin/simulateddata laser_pose_all.bin scan_angles_all.bin ../player_worlds/bitmaps/cave-rotated.png

# visualize ground truth and input data by:
../../bin/visualize_ground_truth laser_pose_all.bin laser_range_all.bin scan_angles_all.bin ../player_worlds/bitmaps/cave-rotated.png laser_reflectance_all.bin

It is different from ../player_sim because it also captures the reflectance
values. 
